-- initial rows (two partitions)
1	0.5
2	0.1
-- DROP PARTITION with an unrepresentable Float64 literal is rejected (fail-closed)
-- nothing was dropped
2
-- an exactly-representable literal resolves the partition
2	0.1
-- the remaining partition is dropped with the exactly-representable value
0
-- a quoted string partition literal is parsed into the partition-key type (rounding); pre-existing behavior
-- only the 0.5 partition remains (the quoted string rounded to the 0.1 partition)
1	0.5
